Best pizza in the world?  No. Good enough (and I'm picky about my pizza)?  Yes.  I'm not saying you should walk here from the Strip, but if you're staying at the Hard Rock or nearby, and want to grab a slice, just walk across the street.  Reasonably priced, quick service, nice guy at the counter.  There is pizza next door at some new place that opened but that's a more upscale restaurant-type place.  Tons of taxi drivers, locals, tourists, even a few families were packing the place.  Open late.  Note - they used to deliver to the Hard Rock but are no longer allowed to (a note at the counter for staff says they will be arrested if they come on site.  Seriously?)

